{"artifact_id":"model_cassette.route.direct_smt.group.m1_no_conflict.overlap.seed-42","artifact_kind":"model_cassette","canonicalization_policy_hash":"sha256:423e189facdecf68a7b2729e2d82e14e7b84f3cd699418a4f4dfe42124fe54c3","content_hash":"sha256:921847bf381e5f678306f5e470a35e36449286fd600d9b7851c77914da2787e3","diagnostics":[],"evidence_status":"evidence_discovery_only","external_effects":["ai"],"input_hashes":[],"origin":"ai_generated","payload":{"constraint_hash":"sha256:d26bbd5b9067a597acdb10855099707677cbfb363229f2bc13242637de0f97f2","model_identity":{"model_id":"qwen2.5-1.5b-instruct","quant":"int4","runtime_version":"openvino-genai-2026.2.1.0-3123-7dea0459b2a"},"output_hex":"","prompt":"Translate a pair of Japanese clinical guideline documents into one SMT query.\u000a\u000aYou are given, for two source documents that may apply to the same situation:\u000a- the Japanese guideline text of each document, after its `document:` id line;\u000a- the group id and the query role to build — either context_overlap (do the two\u000a  guidelines apply to a shared situation?) or deontic_consistency (do their\u000a  obligations agree where they overlap?).\u000a\u000aProduce one query that conforms to the supplied SMT query grammar. Follow these rules:\u000a\u000a- Emit the query in order: a `set-logic` line, a `(set-option :print-success false)`\u000a  line, the role's produce-option line, one `declare-const` per symbol, the `:named`\u000a  assertions, `(check-sat)`, and the closing result command.\u000a- For the context_overlap role, encode whether both guidelines can apply at once, set\u000a  `(set-option :produce-models true)`, and close with `(get-model)`; a sat answer\u000a  reports the shared situation.\u000a- For the deontic_consistency role, encode whether the obligations that co-apply stay\u000a  consistent, set `(set-option :produce-unsat-cores true)`, and close with\u000a  `(get-unsat-core)`; an unsat answer names the conflicting rules through its core.\u000a- Attach every assertion a `:named` label built from the role's scheme: label the\u000a  assertions encoding a document's rules `ctx.<document-id>.rule.<n>` for the\u000a  context_overlap role and `a.<document-id>.rule.<n>` for the deontic_consistency\u000a  role, taking `<document-id>` from that document's `document:` line and numbering\u000a  `<n>` from 0 upward over the document's rules in document order.\u000a- Build terms only from the grammar's forms: `|`-quoted lowercase symbols, `(not …)`,\u000a  `(and …)` and `(or …)` over two or more terms, a comparison `(>= s n)`, `(> s n)`,\u000a  `(<= s n)`, or `(< s n)` of one `Real` symbol `s` against a numeral `n`, and `(- n)`\u000a  for a negative numeral.\u000a- Declare each symbol once, with sort `Bool` or `Real`, before it appears in an assertion.\u000a- Choose logic `QF_UF` for a purely boolean query and `QF_LRA` when the query compares\u000a  `Real` quantities.\u000a\u000aOutput only the query, with nothing before or after it.\u000a\u000agroup: group.m1_no_conflict\u000arole: overlap\u000adocument: test_source.m1_guideline_a\u000a敗血症診療ガイドライン(合成)\u000aCQ1:成人の敗血症患者に対して抗菌薬Aを投与すべきか\u000a成人(18歳以上)の敗血症患者には抗菌薬Aを投与することを推奨する(強い推奨)。\u000aただし、重度腎機能障害のある患者を除く。\u000a用語の定義\u000a用語\u000a定義\u000a成人\u000a18歳以上の患者\u000a小児\u000a18歳未満の患者\u000a重度腎機能障害\u000a高度の腎機能低下を認める状態(合成定義)\u000aエビデンス\u000aランダム化比較試験2件(エビデンスの確実性:中)\u000a観察研究1件(エビデンスの確実性:低)\u000adocument: test_source.m1_control\u000a小児敗血症診療の手引き(合成)\u000a抗菌薬Aの使用\u000a小児(18歳未満)の敗血症患者には抗菌薬Aは禁忌である。","prompt_template_hash":"sha256:8e1fbbed89f60889ef6188e48d73cc86a22fe589e11d6f699528ecd25a666393","route":"route.direct_smt","seed":"42","source":"group.m1_no_conflict.overlap"},"producer":{"pipeline_id":"pipe.m2_direct_smt","pipeline_step_id":"processing_stage.m2.model_fill_smt","toolchain_manifest_hash":"sha256:66894b16254576f70fc56e3e3abf4d489c678e08feaec17e101ec405207b9d84"},"runtime_metadata":{},"schema_id":"schema.model_cassette","schema_version":"ckc.1","trace_refs":[]}